The Ford Mondeo is a car manufactured by Ford since 1993. The first Ford model declared as a "world car",[4][5] the Mondeo was intended to consolidate several Ford model lines worldwide (the European Sierra, the Telstar in Asia and Australia, and the Tempo/Mercury Topaz in North America). The Mondeo nameplate is derived from the Latin word mundus, meaning "world".[6] Thus Mondeo can be viewed as a Latin-derived brandname from multiple languages: Bourguignon monde, English monde, Esperanto mondo, Franco-Provençal mondo, French monde, Friulian mond, Ido mondo, Istriot mondo, Italian mondo, Lombard mond, Occitan mond, Romansh (Surmiran dialect) mundo, Spanish mond, Venetian móndo, Walloon monde, all meaning "world". For its first two generations, the Mondeo was produced using the CDW27 platform, with the third-generation model shifting to the EUCD platform. The fourth-generation models use the CD4 platform, and the fifth-generation use the C2 platform.

Due to declining sales and a growing trend towards crossover SUVs over saloons and estates, Ford announced in March 2021 that it will discontinue the production of the Mondeo in Europe and Argentina with no direct successor.[7][8][9] Production of the Mondeo ended in Europe in March 2022.[10]

v2 Changelog

I've started from scratch for this v2 LORA.

‼ IMPORTANT ‼

📝Biography📝

🌟Mila Azul🌟

whose birth name is Ekaterina Volkova, is a Ukrainian model and musician born on December 1, 1997 in Kiev. She stands at a height of 5'7" (1.70 m) and is known for her buxom and shapely figure, with large natural bosom and a slender build. Mila began her modeling career in 2016 at the age of nineteen and has since worked with various high calibre modeling websites. In addition to modeling, Mila is also a musician. 🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Try the Ultimate SD upscale script!

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

txt2img: A weight of 0.7-0.9 will give the best mix of likeness and flexibility.

Inpainting: A weight of 0.75-85 will give the best low-noise likeness. If you want the absolute best likeness, switch your checkpoint to SD15 since that's the model on which it was trained.

Face restoration: isn't usually necessary, but I recommend setting your face restoration strength inside auto1111 settings to something like 0.7-0.8 which makes the effect less than the default setting of 0.5.

GETTING THE BEST LIKENESS WITH LORA'S

Please add this to the prompt when generating with Swamp Escape. A weight of 1 is fine. The composition will change depending on the weight, so find a weight that is just right.

To use it, simply add it to the prompt.

The effect is to slightly increase the photorealism. However, if the weight is increased to about 0.4 or more, the composition of the original picture will change, so I enjoy Generate by adding it to the prompt with a weight of 1 from the beginning, rather than adding it to the prompt afterwards.

As an aside, I was curious to see what would happen if I used it on an animated model, so I used it with "AnythingV3.0" and found that it did not improve the realism, but rather tightened up the blurry animated picture, which I thought was interesting.

I also found that using "SwampEscapeAA" on the many photorealistic models that are currently available with a perfect sense of realism does not make any sense at all, and the picture is burnt and distorted.

I believe it can be used for other models as well, but at your own risk.

items.name: [LoRA] Shibuya Kanon (Love Live! Superstar!!)
items.description:
Trained using around 150 anime screenshots from season 1 and season 2. 20-30 images are chosen from sideway angles (booru tag from side). This is important, as previous models I trained for Kanon as well as other characters lacked the ability to generate sideway images.

Activation tag: shibuya kanon

To generate school uniform: student uniform, gray dress, red ribbon, neck ribbon, pinafore dress, white shirt

To generate glasses: glasses. For v2, include bangs, hair between eyes as well (the model will generate her wearing glasses without bangs if not prompted)

Notes for v2

This version produces images extremely close to the anime art style. Most importantly, it rarely distorts her eyes. The key to this might be using a high repeat number and low learning rate, as well as a large enough LoRA capacity (I used 32/16). See changelog (About this version section on the left pane) for more details regarding the training parameters.

Model and ratio:

  • Meina_Hentai*: around 0.6-0.7. I recommend using this since it is what the LoRA has been fine-tuned from. Do not get fooled by the name, it is actually a good SFW model

  • Anything v4.5, AOMv3: similar to the above. Also precisely describes Kanon, though generated images have high saturation

Demo images did not went through any highres upscaler.

Notes for v1

Model and ratio:

  • Anything v4.5: use a LoRA ratio of around 0.6-0.8

  • Corneos7thHeavenMix: ratio about 0.7-0.8. Good for generating anime style art

  • AOM3A1: around 0.6. Might confuse left and right bangs if generate sideway images

AOM3A1 also has the tendency to change Kanon's hairstyle to hair bun, hair tie, or add random hair bow, ornament, etc. Consider adding those to the negative prompt if you don't want them to appear in your images.

Comparing v2 and v1

Left: v1, right: v2. All images are generated with Meina_Hentai and AOMv3 VAE

items.name: Myne Factory - Ascendance Of A Bookworm
items.description:
Ascendance Of A Bookworm

Authors: Juusoz, Tylenol, Goldkoron and Expl0dingCat

Feel free to join our Discord community for updates on current models or models on other shows.

Prompt Format

The prompts we trained on are available in the corresponding T{version} prompt list.txt file.

T3.2 Prompt list.txt

Format: Parent tag, description prompt 1, description prompt 2, etc;

The parent tag serves as the primary label for the overall theme of the image and acts as the main subject. The description prompts are a comprehensive list of attributes, objects, actions, and other elements that describe the subject in detail. Each subject is separated by a semicolon (;) while the individual attributes, objects, actions, and elements are separated by a comma (,).

Example:

Positive prompts: MFB Style; 1boy; 1girl; Lutz; Myne, poor, yellow eyes, blue hair, hairstick; (masterpiece); detailed; reflective; depth of field; 8k; photo;

Negative prompts: (bad hands, error), bad anatomy, low quality, worst quality, watermark, signature, poorly drawn face, noise, grain, nude, naked, upskirt, blind, AOB Style, solo

Just because we haven’t trained on something doesn’t mean the base AI model doesn’t already know what it is, so go crazy.

Style tags:

You can specify what style the image should generate in using the following tags.

MyneFactoryBase style, for more artistic pictures MFB Style

Ascendance of a Bookworm style, for more anime accurate pictures AOB Style

Recommended Settings

  • Sampling Steps 40

  • Sampler DPM++ SDE Karras

  • Image Size At least 768x768

  • CFG 7

  • Clip skip 1 (settings, Clip skip)

Created by GeomanticArts

Coco Bandicoot has proved to be an elusive LoRA, but lets fix that! An old school classic game and some underappreciated characters, lets spread the love around.

Coco's hair is pretty powerful and despite being in 95% of the training images it's not really captured consistently at all. It seems to think it's a ponytail. (huge ahoge) helps, but pretty often you get just a ponytail appearance. This one was trained with pretty aggressive settings for the LoRAs I normally post mostly to try and get that hair to be more consistent. Anyone with tips about this it would be appreciated.

Example images all made with AOM2-7thV3_C_40 at weight 1

'Coco Bandicoot, furry female, overalls, white shirt, huge ahoge' - Example prompt
